I use GEEZ (mini, 7A) as a shortening of Gee Whiz.

@Pagrisan

Quite the opposite.  It is not anyone's nickname.  It is what is called a minced oath.  Words like these, including also gee, gee whiz, dagnabbit, gosh, goshdarnit, heck, fudge, shish kebab, and so many others, are used specifically not to say the names and words that should not be said (or taken in vain) in polite company.

What's more, what that someone that a bunch of us worship did not pronounce his own name anything like GEEZ.

